theorem union_of_interiors_subset_interior_union {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    (interior (A : Set X) ∪ interior (B : Set X)) ⊆ interior (A ∪ B : Set X) := by
  -- The set on the left is open.
  have hOpen : IsOpen (interior (A : Set X) ∪ interior (B : Set X)) :=
    (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior (A : Set X)))
      .union (isOpen_interior : IsOpen (interior (B : Set X)))
  -- It is contained in `A ∪ B`.
  have hSub : (interior (A : Set X) ∪ interior (B : Set X)) ⊆ (A ∪ B : Set X) := by
    intro x hx
    cases hx with
    | inl hxA => exact Or.inl (interior_subset hxA)
    | inr hxB => exact Or.inr (interior_subset hxB)
  -- By maximality of the interior, we obtain the desired inclusion.
  exact interior_maximal hSub hOpen

theorem isOpen_interior_union {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hB : IsOpen (B : Set X)) :
    IsOpen ((interior (A : Set X)) ∪ B) := by
  have hA : IsOpen (interior (A : Set X)) := isOpen_interior
  exact hA.union hB
